Hello Matteo,

Heritrix transforms urls into a canonical form to check whether they have already been seen. For example, these urls are all different by default:

http://foo.com/page.php?parameter=bar
http://foo.com/page.php?parameter=baz
http://foo.com/page.php?param=bar

But these are considered equivalent:

http://foo.com/page.php?x=bar&y=baz
http://foo.com/page.php?y=baz&x=bar

Hope that gives you an idea.

The rules are customizable as well. There is more information here: https://webarchive.jira.com/wiki/display/Heritrix/URI+Canonicalization+Rules

Noah



